item.title: 4 Different Chinese Girl Looks
item.description:
4 Different Chinese Girl Looks
You do not have to be Chinese to wear these looks! Haha, the reason for the title is because while I was in Beijing for a PR event for Lancome, I was asked by the Lancome fans in China to create 4 simple but different Chinese girl looks. A simple look, an office look, a dating look and a party look. I also decided to also use the eyeshadow sponge applicators and fingers because this is a very popular way to apply makeup (rather than brushes). Each look is very wearable, sweet and simple. Please enjoy! FYI, this was also filmed with my old Canon camcorder, not my new one. So it's not as HD as my other videos. Also, the reason why I had to compromise a lot of products (like the eyeliner blow dryer part) was because I wasn't given a lot of products. (Notice how I use some of the same products over and over?) But, that's a good thing because this just comes to show you how you don't need a suitcase full of makeup to create different looks :) Music by A-mei Yi Ye Qing Olivia Ong Fly me to the Moon RoBERT Ange ou demon Official music video here http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jibxphtDZSk I'll write down the list of all the products tomorrow. It's super late here and I'm so tired =( This video was not sponsored. This is not my official Lancome video of the month. This was suppose to be released in China, but I decided why not upload it here?

item.title: Elongated Eyes (Son Ga-in inspired)
item.description:
Elongated Eyes (Son Ga-in inspired)
Hey guys (Btw- apologies if I pronounce Ga-In's name wrong.. I jus know her as Yeobo/Noona from WGM episodes tehehee) Yep- still ill. It's been a month & a half... but getting better ^_^. As requested- this look is inspired by Son Ga-In from Brown Eyed Girls. There are two looks combined in one video. Both looks concentrates on elongated eyes by exaggerating the length of the peepers. One is great for daytime; simple, chic yet edgy. The other look is dangerous, intense and great for clubbing/partying. Btw- this look is jus inspired by the Ga-In, I am not applying I look like her. I have to say both of these looks are not what I would normally wear lol but I adore Ga-In. She is petite yet sexy! Such a talented cool chick from an awesome band and it just inspired me to experiment with 'dangerous looking eyes'. I don't have monolids like the beautiful Ga-In but I wanted to demonstrate that this look is versatile and looks great on all eye sizes and shapes. My eyes are rounder than Ga-in's therefore her eyes look sharper. Each person's eyes gives a different effect. Ga-In sports different eyeliner looks. One is her winged eyeliner but I figured there are a lot of amazing tutorials on the web already so I figured I'll choose the more exaggerated look. As for the night look- I decided to base it on her Baby-G ad. If you keep up with me on twitter or the Bubzbeauty Facebook Page; you guys will know that 'We Got Married' is one of my fav shows to watch. The adam couple (Jo Kwon & Ga In) are my fav couple because they are so cute and so hilarious. I cried my eyes out when they aired the last episode last week. I miss them so much! ADAM COUPLE FTW! In the meanwhile- I do have the Khuntoria couple to keep me smiling tehehe.... I'm still working on the lighting in the makeup room so bare with me. I make tutorials with a lamp shining infront of me so the face appears yellower because the light (which is yellow) reflects on my face. Big thank you to Youtuber 'GPBEATZ' for the '2AM- I was wrong' instrumental and also to youtuber 'HolyAugust' for the 'Son Ga-In Irreversible' instrumental. Check out their channels ^_^ http://www.youtube.com/gpbeatz http://www.youtube.com/holyaugust Until next time, Stay well guys!
